Check options (e.g. do defaults match upstream)
make functions take options as nullable, as this equates with the defaults
Use a raw.zig built from each release to make sure version flags are complete
Check every extern structs size
Use hasdecl to compile error instead of needing version

Use bitjuggle package

Change this pattern:
    var buf: raw.git_buf = undefined;
    try internal.wrapCall("git_commit_header_field", .{ &buf, internal.toC(self), field.ptr });
    const ret = internal.fromC(buf);
    return ret;

Into this:
    var buf: git.Buf = undefined;
    try internal.wrapCall("git_commit_header_field", .{ internal.toC(&buf), internal.toC(self), field.ptr });
    return buf;
